{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/anomaly-detection-made-simple-70775c914377", "time": 1683006611.825553, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/anomaly-detection-made-simple-70775c914377/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Anomaly Detection made simple. Credit card fraud case using pycaret\u2026 | by Amalesh Vemula | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Anomaly Detection made simple", "description": "In this new era of banking, financial payment services giants like Stripe, Square etc, made credit card payments seamless and the credit card transactions have been increasing by multiples every\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.creditcards.com/credit-card-news/market-share-statistics.php", "anchor_text": "source", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://www.fool.com/the-ascent/research/identity-theft-credit-card-fraud-statistics/", "anchor_text": "source", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://www.kaggle.com/*Your-Username*/account)", "anchor_text": "https://www.kaggle.com/*Your-Username*/account)", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1tlW9QZwJSYD1OCWt8lWTimfDw_EcKuP7#scrollTo=hI9a8EOzTRN1", "anchor_text": "colab", "paragraph_index": 24}], "all_paragraphs": ["In this new era of banking, financial payment services giants like Stripe, Square etc, made credit card payments seamless and the credit card transactions have been increasing by multiples every year\u00b9 (source). Thus also resulting in Credit card fraud reports doubling every year\u00b2 (source).", "An Anomaly is something that deviates from what is normal or expected. In credit card transactions, most of the fraudulent cases deviate from the behavior of a normal transaction. It's subjective to say what normal transaction behavior is but there are different types of anomaly detection techniques to find this behavior\u00b3. Here we\u2019ll be discussing three types of techniques.", "I\u2019m considering the kaggle Credit Card Fraud Detection for carrying out anomaly detection\u2074.", "Downloading the datasets from API calls:", "First download your API token by going to your Kaggle My Account (https://www.kaggle.com/*Your-Username*/account), going to section \u2018API\u2019 and clicking on \u2018create new API token\u2019. You will now download a file called \u2018kaggle.json\u2019. You have to upload this file to your colab notebook.", "You can now use the code given below to download and unzip the dataset.", "In the given dataset there are 492 frauds out of 284,807 transactions, I\u2019m considering a sample of 0.1 for our analysis without losing outlier fraction for further unsupervised learning. The outlier fraction is 0.001723.", "Setup to initialize the environment in pycaret\u2075 and creates the transformation pipeline to prepare the data for modeling and deployment.", "The Isolation forest algorithm segregates observations by randomly selecting a feature and then randomly selecting a split value between the maximum and minimum values of selected feature similarly constructing the separation by creating random decision trees\u2076. Thus, an anomaly score is calculated as the number of conditions required to separate a given observation.", "We can build the model using create_model function in pycaret package, one can modify the parameters accordingly using the following code.", "Finding Isolation forest anomaly scores and labels using assign_model\u2077 function.", "In Angle-based outlier detection addresses the problem of high-dimensionality by comparing angles between pairs of distance vectors to consider as an anomaly rather than using distance directly\u2078.", "We can build the model using create_model function in pycaret package, one can modify the parameters accordingly using the following code.", "Finding ABOD scores and labels using assign_model function.", "ROC_AUC for the Angle-based outlier detection is 0.777.", "The Subspace outliers are identified by finding localized regions of the data in low-dimensional space that have abnormally low density\u2079.", "We can build the model using create_model function in pycaret package, one can modify the parameters accordingly using the following code.", "Finding SOD scores and labels using assign_model function.", "ROC_AUC for the Subspace outlier detection is 0.942.", "This is one of the most robust way of finding outliers where it considers using robust estimator called MCD estimator. This illustrates the masking effect: the classical estimates can be so strongly affected by contamination that diagnostic tools such as the Mahalanobis distances become unable to detect the outliers\u00b9\u2070. As the robust distances are not sensitive to the masking effect, they can be used to flag the outliers\u00b9\u00b9.", "We can build the model using create_model function in pycaret package, one can modify the parameters accordingly using the following code.", "Finding MCD anomaly scores and labels using assign_model function.", "ROC_AUC for the Minimum Covariance Determinant outlier detection is 0.906.", "From all the four anomaly detection techniques for this kaggle credit fraud detection dataset, we see that according to the ROC_AUC, Subspace outlier detection comparatively gives better result.", "Please check the detailed code of these anomaly detection techniques from this colab.", "Most of the Banks and payment services using different anomaly scoring methods either using one anomaly score or averaging the scaled anomaly scores of some of anomaly scoring techniques to make sure not to lose any fraudulent transactions.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F70775c914377&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operat